"Industry Idle is a resource management game where you build factories🏭, produce goods📦 and make money💸.

Let's go through some basic concepts to get you started - it won't take long, I pinky promise."

"All buildings need power⚡, you have a wind turbine that generates power. You can see your current power supply on the left side of the top bar.

You might have noticed that wind turbines only work 80% of the time. You can consider building other types of power plants that generate stable power."

"You have a lot of resource deposits on the map. To extract resources, you have to build mines⛏️ on top of the corresponding deposit.

For example, you have an oil well🛢️ that extracts oil from an oil deposit.

Resource deposits are unlimited - no need to worry about them running out. Apart from mines, other buildings can be built on any empty tile."

"Resource transportation costs fuel. On this map, you can use petrol⛽ as fuel. You have an oil refinery that transports oil from the oil well and produces petrol.

The tiny moving dots represent the real-time movement of resources. You should optimize your building locations to minimize the distance of travel.

Upgrading your buildings will increase their output, but will also increase their power usage and input required.

You can change your fuel type in the transportation center🚦. Remember to make sure your fuel production is above consumption otherwise your production will halt when you run out of fuel."

"To make money, you need to export your resources via the trade center. To do this, simply turn on auto sell for that resource.

You can also buy resources from the trade center as well. Remember if you buy a resource, you will drive up the price and if you sell a resource, you will drive down the price.

The market is volatile and the price📈 changes regularly."

"To build new buildings, you need to unlock it first in the research lab🧪. The research lab also converts science to research points.

Your wind turbine (and other power plants) produces a small amount of science when running. And you can build school🏫 and other dedicated buildings to boost science later.

Now you have learned all the basics, start to build up your economy! Here are some cash💸 and petrol⛽ to give you a jump start."
